The loss of music icon, Johnny Clegg, is being felt around the world. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG – Legendary South African singer Johnny Clegg has been laid to rest in a private funeral. Clegg, who died on Tuesday, was buried on Wednesday afternoon at Westpark Cemetery in Johannesburg. READ: South Africans react to Johnny Clegg's death Clegg’s manager Roddy Quin said it was the late musician’s wish to have a private burial. “Johnny was buried yesterday (Wednesday) at 16h30, just with his family and some of the band members, it was a very private affair which is what the family requested and it was also Johnny’s request,” Quin said. READ: Hamba kahle dad: Jesse Clegg pays tribute to his father Quin said details about public memorial services will be announced soon. The 66-year-old died on Tuesday after a long battle with pancreatic cancer.